metadata.name: Hatchet: Magarikuneri #6
metadata.description:
Hatchet: Magarikuneri (曲がりくねり) is the second piece in Hatchet; a generative art series that hatches an arrangement of segmented polygons generated via a Voronoi diagram. Magarikuneri (Japanese for 'winding/twisting') arranges it's polygons in twisting spirals that are far more chaotic than Hatchet: Uzumaki. The piece will cycle through varying color intensities, resetting upon encountering a twist. There is also a small chance the background will be dark instead of light; allowing for the same palettes to be seen through a different lens.

All pieces in Hatchet are composed to emulate the aesthetic of colored pencils on paper. Each piece is capable of exporting its hatch lines as a well-labeled SVG document. This will allow collectors interested in plotting to create physical renditions of their iteration.

The following key-press actions are supported on the token:
- 'r': Animate the erasure and re-drawing of the hatch lines.
- 's': Export the SVG document describing the arrangement of hatch lines.

metadata.name: Lush Fields  #25
metadata.description:
* fixed version * 

Lush Fields puts you in a space far from home,fluffy,lush grass under you ... and lots of space in front of you.

Lush Fields was created as an offshoot from upcoming works, because the minimalistic focus on the grass, light and brushy haptics has a charm on its own.

Still there are lots of parameters which can change.. colours, direction of light, positions, variety
 Of the ground modulations etc.

I hope you have a good mint .. and if you are not satisfied: try another one :)

metadata.name: V.Mountains #145
metadata.description:
V.Mountains is an abstract representation of the turbulence and chaos of our life.



The mountain is a symbol of the way that life is constantly in flux,

of the way that we are constantly trying to make sense of the world around us.



The mountain is a source of inspiration, a place of refuge, a source of strength.

It is a place where we can go to reflect on our lives, to find peace and solace.



The mountain is a symbol of hope.

It is a reminder that, no matter how dark and cold the world may be, there is always a chance for new beginnings.



The mountain is a symbol of the human spirit, and of our ability to persevere in the face of adversity.

It is a representation of our journey through life, with all of its ups and downs.

It is a reminder that, no matter how difficult the path may be,
we can always reach the summit if we are willing to put in the hard work.



Created in Vanilla Javascript.


S - to download image.


Libraries used:

noise.js by Joseph Gentle.
Javascript-Voronoi by Raymond Hill.
